children.subject:
I want this guy to teach me the ropes of recruiting.

Guaranteed he got FAANG/HFT/Unicorn offers but chose to create a web3 start up instead

history.content:
Hello y'all!

RECRUITING, DECLASSIFIED: Join us for an evening workshop to help you start your career in tech! Blueprint and Codebase are bringing in companies and alumni who are now making waves in industry. Whether you're interested in Software Engineering, Product Design, Product Management, or even startups, come on out and hear from these Cal alumni who sat in our shoes a few years ago.

We'll be giving a crash course into recruiting before shifting into a panel where our panelist shares their advice and experiences in recruiting, as well as in industry. Lastly, we'll be having small breakout groups where students can network with companies and alumni!

If you're curious about how to start your professional career, I encourage y'all to come out! The event was created for students like me who hadn't been exposed to recruiting before! All are welcome! It's gonna be tomorrow at 5-7pm in Wozniak Lounge!

EVENT DETAILS
Name: Recruiting Declassified
Location: Wozniak Lounge, Soda Hall
Time: April 27th, 5-7 PM
FB Event: <https://fb.me/e/4KlqyEixg>
